metadata.name: Unbalanced Life #11
metadata.description:
Most of the time we don't know what we do with our lives, we try hard and make decisions hoping for the best. We could go from a balanced and well-directed life to a disastrous and shattered one.

"Unbalanced Life" is an abstraction of these aspects. Each line represents a stage in your life. Over each line are "life decisions" that you take. Several are well defined, others are just a mess and explode, like in real life! 

The life type will be included below in the right corner unless your life is seriously "Shattered", then the name will be huge enough to punch you right in the face, or you could get "No Life" and with that, a disappointing tag will remember you that at less your life is better than this NFT.

What kind of life will you get?

You will face these challenging features:

Life types
- Shattered life
- Unbalanced life
- Balanced life
- Wasted life
- Lack of life
- No life 

Four color schemes
- Groovy seventies
- Rad 80's
- Fire and fury
- Outstanding carbon

Well-thought decisions
- Boolean

metadata.name: Perpetual Oscillations  #68
metadata.description:
Planes expand and contract over time in different rhythms. 

Display notes:
The work is intended to be viewed running live in the browser, and there is no set aspect ratio. The viewer is invited to explore the space and choose their viewpoint. 

Controls:
Left-clicking and dragging - rotate around the center 
right-clicking and dragging - pan around the space 
Scrolling - zoom in and out 
Press b - b-side 
Press o - go back to the origin 
Press 1 to 3 - change the pixel density
Adjusting pixel density or changing the screen size will bring you back to the origin. 

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: CityScape: Istanbul #88
metadata.description:
Istanbul is a city that straddles the Bosporus Strait, and lies in both Europe and Asia, with a population of over 15 million residents. Most of the population is located in big iconic hills known as the "Seven Hills of Istanbul". 

   In this project, I tried to capture and interpret the daily life routine of the people who live in these hills with the viewing point from Bosphorus. There are three camera angle possibilities to examine the details in different layers. Also, building types, the slope of the hill, and green area density vary in between those scenarios. There are two time zones: day and night. In the night scene, there is a possibility to obtain the crescent moon which is the symbol of the culture inhabits in these lands.

To save as a high-quality image, open in live view and click yes on the incoming prompt.

Created with p5js

metadata.name: Colorfall #103
metadata.description:
My first attempt at a generative NFT. This started with an idea to create a grid of diagonal lines with the basic line function of p5js. I had discarded this idea until my friend said it looked like a waterfall of colors and he liked it, so I decided to mint it. After tweaking some parameters like colors and line thickness it produced some nice outputs.

I hope you will enjoy it. Free mint(unless you cant wait and want to pay =) plus 25% royalties for minters.

reserves for the collectors of my testnft on objkt, my friend CampendonkP and a few artists who I remembered who did free mints, like punevyr and JohnRising.

metadata.name: Collage #243
metadata.description:
Inspired by traditional Japanese wagami design. We use the iconic patterns of our previous projects to recreate this artwork. All the patterns are generated first and then used to build the scene. 

In this project Aluan brings his delicate texture from his 'Chaos' series, Jinyao brings his beloved pattern from the 'Cloud' series and Wen brings his iconic pattern from the 'Maze'. 'Collage' is not just about mixing our style, but it is also about finding harmony among all the elements. 'Collage' is also about working together, in that we can create something that's difficult to achieve or imagine if we were working alone.

Each piece contains the patterns of all the 3 artists, each artist has a certain number of patterns with different colors. Depending which artist you get, his pattern will be shown as the primary color theme while the pattern of the other 2 artists turns into grayscale to make the primary pattern with color stand out. 

There are 7 different scenes included in this project, which are : Mountains, Waves, Lake, Hexagons, Tetrapods, Chrysanthemums and Lotus. We took great inspiration from the traditional Japanese design, and we discovered these are some of the most common elements in it. Therefore we decide to use them and reimagine them by mixing our patterns. 

The title 'Collage' doesn't only apply to the visual style, but also to the code as well. In this project we mixed p5.js and Vanilla JS. While Aluan and Jinyao work with their patterns in p5. Wen gathered the patterns and recreated the full scene in Vanilla JS.
